<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1910-08-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1910-08-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="815" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d815">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Consul <persName type="from">Olivares</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi><note n="1" xml:id="d815fn1">Transmitted through the American Legation at
                                Tegucigalpa.</note></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Extract—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Managua</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-08-28"><hi rend="italic">August 28,
                                1910</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Mr. Olivares reports that Gens. Juan Estrada and Emiliano Chamorro
                            arrived at Nicaragua at 6 o’clock p.m. to-day.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>